name: Taro tapioca coconut dessert
ingredients:
- tapioca pearls: 1 cup
- water:
- Taro root: 2 cups, peeled and 1cm cubes
- Coconut milk: 1 can
- Rock sugar: 0.66 cup
steps:
- Boil 4 cups of water, add tapioca pearls. Simmer for about 7 minutes.
- Cover then pan and stand for 10 to 15 minutes. Pearls should become transparent. Drain and set aside.
- Boil 6 cups of water. Stir in taro root. Simmer for about 10 minutes until soft.
- Add coconut milk, rock sugar. Simmer for 20 minutes.
- Mix in pearls. Serve hot, room temperature or chilled.
